(991, 4, '2013-01-29 13:23:43', '2013-01-29 12:23:43', 'Auszug aus  »A piece of Sky«, Soundtrack zum Film »Yentl«\nLyrics: Alan and Marilyn Bergman \n\nTell me where \nWhere is it written \nWhat is it I meant to be? \nThat I can''t dare... \n\nIt all began the day I found \nThat from my window I could only see \nA piece of sky. \nI stepped outside and looked around. \nI never dreamed it was so wide \nOr even half as high. \nThe time had come \nTo try my wings \nAnd even thought it seemed at any moment I could fall, \nI felt the most, \nAmazing things, \nThe things you can''t imagine \nif you''ve never flown at all. \nThough it''s safer to stay on the ground, \nSometimes where danger lies \nThere the sweetest of pleasures are found. \nNo matter where I go, \nThere''ll be memories that tug at my sleeve, \nBut there will also be \nMore to question, yet more to believe.. \n\nThe more I live - the more I learn. \nThe more I learn - the more I realize \nThe less I know. \nEach step I take - \nEach page I turn - \nEach mile I travel only means \nThe more I have to go. \nWhat''s wrong with wanting more? \n\nIf you can fly - then soar! \n\nWith all there is - why settle for \njust a piece of sky? \n\n…nun Auf - die Welt entdecken - guten Mutes mit gespreizten Federn! \nEin wundervolles und fabelhaftes Leben wünsche ich Ihnen.', 'Gabi Schwab-Trapp', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '944-autosave', '', '', '2013-01-29 13:23:43', '2013-01-29 12:23:43', '', 944, 'http://werkschau.hs-augsburg.de/ss_13/944-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
